  "body": "I have a repository index with relative paths:\r\n```\r\n  spark:\r\n  - apiVersion: v1\r\n    created: 2017-11-20T08:24:41.035796831Z\r\n    description: A Helm chart for Kubernetes\r\n    digest: 7d9c80037b56ef684dd0805d0c1f9a7ac36139a8aa331035844e82a7c229e3a1\r\n    name: spark\r\n    urls:\r\n    - spark-0.1.1.tgz\r\n    version: 0.1.1\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhen I run `helm install spark --repo http://my-helm-repo` I get \r\n```\r\nError: Non-absolute URLs should be in form of repo_name/path_to_chart, got: spark-0.1.1.tgz\r\n``` \r\n\r\nI expected that the chart would be resolved relative to the repo url, but they apparently it did not.\r\n\r\nTested with helm 2.6.2, 2.7.0 and 2.7.2.",
